usdL2tpMIB.name: usdL2tpMIB

revisions.description: Added new objects usdL2tpSysConfigTunnelSwitchingEnabled, usdL2tpSysConfigControlRetransmissions, usdL2tpSysConfigTunnelIdleTimeout.

Added usdL2tpSessionStatusLacTunneledIfIndex as long-term replacement for usdL2tpSessionStatusLacPppIfIndex. Added new objects usdL2tpTunnelStatusCumEstabTime, usdL2tpSessionStatusCumEstabTime, usdL2tpSessionStatPayLostPackets. Changed range of usdL2tpSysConfigDestructTimeout to 10-3600.
Initial revision, based in part on IETF L2TP Working Group draft-ietf-l2tpext-l2tp-mib-01.

usdL2tpMIB.contactinfo: Unisphere Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdL2tpMIB.description: The L2TP MIB for the Unisphere Networks enterprise.

UsdL2tpTunnelId.name: UsdL2tpTunnelId
UsdL2tpTunnelId.description: An L2TP Tunnel ID. Implementation constraints may restrict the range of values actually used.

UsdL2tpSessionId.name: UsdL2tpSessionId
UsdL2tpSessionId.description: An L2TP Session ID. Implementation constraints may restrict the range of values actually used.

UsdL2tpAdminState.name: UsdL2tpAdminState
UsdL2tpAdminState.description: The administrative state exerted on L2TP tunnels sessions at some scope of control. enabled New tunnels/sessions may be instantiated. disabled All tunnels/sessions are terminated. drain No new tunnels/sessions may be instantiated, but any existing tunnels/sessions may persist until they expire by other means. The DESCRIPTION clause of an object defined to have this syntax must describe the scope of control that object exerts (e.g., all tunnels/sessions across the system, sessions within a single tunnel, etc.).

UsdL2tpTransport.name: UsdL2tpTransport
UsdL2tpTransport.description: Transport type over which L2TP is carried.

usdL2tpSysConfigAdminState.name: usdL2tpSysConfigAdminState
usdL2tpSysConfigAdminState.description: Exerts control over all L2TP tunnels/sessions in the system.

usdL2tpSysConfigDestructTimeout.name: usdL2tpSysConfigDestructTimeout
usdL2tpSysConfigDestructTimeout.description: The amount of time, in seconds, to preserve dynamic tunnels/sessions after they become inactive, e.g. to poll their statistics.

usdL2tpSysConfigIpChecksumEnable.name: usdL2tpSysConfigIpChecksumEnable
usdL2tpSysConfigIpChecksumEnable.description: Enable/disable IP checksumming for tunnels with UDP/IP transport.

usdL2tpSysConfigControlRetransmissions.name: usdL2tpSysConfigControlRetransmissions
usdL2tpSysConfigControlRetransmissions.description: The number of retransmission retries allowed before control session goes down.

usdL2tpSysConfigTunnelIdleTimeout.name: usdL2tpSysConfigTunnelIdleTimeout
usdL2tpSysConfigTunnelIdleTimeout.description: Idle tunnel remains active for the specified amount of time; value 0 disables the timer i.e. tunnel becomes persistent.

usdL2tpSysConfigReceiveDataSequencingIgn.name: usdL2tpSysConfigReceiveDataSequencingIgnore
usdL2tpSysConfigReceiveDataSequencingIgn.description: Enable/disable ignoring of receive sequencing of L2TP data packets.

usdL2tpSysStatusProtocolVersion.name: usdL2tpSysStatusProtocolVersion
usdL2tpSysStatusProtocolVersion.description: Vector of supported L2TP protocol version and revision numbers. Supported versions are identified via a two octet pairing where the first octet indicates the version and the second octet contains the revision.

usdL2tpSysStatusVendorName.name: usdL2tpSysStatusVendorName
usdL2tpSysStatusVendorName.description: Vendor name of the L2TP protocol stack.

usdL2tpSysStatusFirmwareRev.name: usdL2tpSysStatusFirmwareRev
usdL2tpSysStatusFirmwareRev.description: Firmware revision for the L2TP protocol stack.

usdL2tpSysStatusFailedDestinations.name: usdL2tpSysStatusFailedDestinations
usdL2tpSysStatusFailedDestinations.description: Number of destination creation attempts that failed.

usdL2tpSysStatusActiveDestinations.name: usdL2tpSysStatusActiveDestinations
usdL2tpSysStatusActiveDestinations.description: Number of destinations having at least one active tunnel.

usdL2tpSysStatusFailedTunnels.name: usdL2tpSysStatusFailedTunnels
usdL2tpSysStatusFailedTunnels.description: Number of tunnel creation attempts that failed to reach the established state.

usdL2tpSysStatusFailedTunnelAuthens.name: usdL2tpSysStatusFailedTunnelAuthens
usdL2tpSysStatusFailedTunnelAuthens.description: Number of tunnel creation attempts that failed authentication.

usdL2tpSysStatusFailedSessions.name: usdL2tpSysStatusFailedSessions
usdL2tpSysStatusFailedSessions.description: Number of session creation attempts that failed to reach the established state.

usdL2tpDestConfigTable.name: usdL2tpDestConfigTable
usdL2tpDestConfigTable.description: The L2TP destination configuration table. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in usdL2tpDestStatsTable.

usdL2tpDestConfigEntry.name: usdL2tpDestConfigEntry
usdL2tpDestConfigEntry.description: Describes the configuration attributes of an L2TP destination.

usdL2tpDestConfigIfIndex.name: usdL2tpDestConfigIfIndex
usdL2tpDestConfigIfIndex.description: Same value as ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

usdL2tpDestConfigRowStatus.name: usdL2tpDestConfigRowStatus
usdL2tpDestConfigRowStatus.description: An implementation may choose not to support administrative configuration of tunnels.

usdL2tpDestStatusTable.name: usdL2tpDestStatusTable
usdL2tpDestStatusTable.description: The L2TP destination status table. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in usdL2tpDestConfigTable.

usdL2tpDestStatusEntry.name: usdL2tpDestStatusEntry
usdL2tpDestStatusEntry.description: Describes the status attributes of an L2TP destination.

usdL2tpDestStatusIfIndex.name: usdL2tpDestStatusIfIndex
usdL2tpDestStatusIfIndex.description: Same value as ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

usdL2tpDestStatusTransport.name: usdL2tpDestStatusTransport
usdL2tpDestStatusTransport.description: The underlying transport over which this L2TP destination is carried.

usdL2tpDestStatusEffectiveAdminState.name: usdL2tpDestStatusEffectiveAdminState
usdL2tpDestStatusEffectiveAdminState.description: The administrative state currently in effect. This could be the configured admin state for this destination, or an overriding admin state exerted from a higher hierarchical level (system).

usdL2tpDestStatusFailedTunnels.name: usdL2tpDestStatusFailedTunnels
usdL2tpDestStatusFailedTunnels.description: Number of tunnel creation attempts that failed to reach the established state.

usdL2tpDestStatusFailedTunnelAuthens.name: usdL2tpDestStatusFailedTunnelAuthens
usdL2tpDestStatusFailedTunnelAuthens.description: Number of tunnel creation attempts that failed authentication.

usdL2tpDestStatusFailedSessions.name: usdL2tpDestStatusFailedSessions
usdL2tpDestStatusFailedSessions.description: Number of session creation attempts that failed to reach the established state.

usdL2tpDestStatTable.name: usdL2tpDestStatTable
usdL2tpDestStatTable.description: The L2TP destination statistics table. Describes the aggregate control and payload statistics for all L2TP tunnels configured on each destination. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in usdL2tpDestConfigTable.

usdL2tpDestStatEntry.name: usdL2tpDestStatEntry
usdL2tpDestStatEntry.description: Describes the aggregate L2TP control and payload statistics for all L2TP tunnels on an L2TP destination.

usdL2tpDestStatIfIndex.name: usdL2tpDestStatIfIndex
usdL2tpDestStatIfIndex.description: Same value as ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

usdL2tpDestStatCtlRecvErrors.name: usdL2tpDestStatCtlRecvErrors
usdL2tpDestStatCtlRecvErrors.description: Number of control packets incurring reception errors.

usdL2tpDestStatCtlRecvDiscards.name: usdL2tpDestStatCtlRecvDiscards
usdL2tpDestStatCtlRecvDiscards.description: Number of control packets discarded after reception.

usdL2tpDestStatCtlSendErrors.name: usdL2tpDestStatCtlSendErrors
usdL2tpDestStatCtlSendErrors.description: Number of control packets incurring transmission errors.

usdL2tpDestStatCtlSendDiscards.name: usdL2tpDestStatCtlSendDiscards
usdL2tpDestStatCtlSendDiscards.description: Number of control packets discarded before transmission.

usdL2tpDestStatPayRecvErrors.name: usdL2tpDestStatPayRecvErrors
usdL2tpDestStatPayRecvErrors.description: Number of payload packets incurring reception errors.

usdL2tpDestStatPayRecvDiscards.name: usdL2tpDestStatPayRecvDiscards
usdL2tpDestStatPayRecvDiscards.description: Number of payload packets discarded after reception.

usdL2tpDestStatPaySendErrors.name: usdL2tpDestStatPaySendErrors
usdL2tpDestStatPaySendErrors.description: Number of payload packets incurring transmission errors.

usdL2tpDestStatPaySendDiscards.name: usdL2tpDestStatPaySendDiscards
usdL2tpDestStatPaySendDiscards.description: Number of payload packets discarded before transmission.

usdL2tpTunnelConfigTable.name: usdL2tpTunnelConfigTable
usdL2tpTunnelConfigTable.description: The L2TP tunnel configuration table. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in usdL2tpTunnelStatsTable.

usdL2tpTunnelConfigEntry.name: usdL2tpTunnelConfigEntry
usdL2tpTunnelConfigEntry.description: Describes the configuration attributes of an L2TP tunnel.

usdL2tpTunnelConfigIfIndex.name: usdL2tpTunnelConfigIfIndex
usdL2tpTunnelConfigIfIndex.description: Same value as ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

usdL2tpTunnelConfigRowStatus.name: usdL2tpTunnelConfigRowStatus
usdL2tpTunnelConfigRowStatus.description: An implementation may choose not to support administrative configuration of tunnels.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusTable.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusTable
usdL2tpTunnelStatusTable.description: The L2TP tunnel status and statistics table. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in usdL2tpTunnelConfigTable.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusEntry.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusEntry
usdL2tpTunnelStatusEntry.description: An L2TP tunnel interface stats entry.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusIfIndex.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusIfIndex
usdL2tpTunnelStatusIfIndex.description: Same as the value of ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusTransport.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusTransport
usdL2tpTunnelStatusTransport.description: The underlying transport over which this L2TP tunnel is carried.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusEffectiveAdminState.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusEffectiveAdminState
usdL2tpTunnelStatusEffectiveAdminState.description: The administrative state currently in effect. This could be the configured admin state for this tunnel, or an overriding admin state exerted from a higher hierarchical level (system, destination).

usdL2tpTunnelStatusState.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusState
usdL2tpTunnelStatusState.description: The current state of the tunnel.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusInitiated.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusInitiated
usdL2tpTunnelStatusInitiated.description: Indicates whether the tunnel was initiated locally, or by the remote tunnel peer.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteHostName.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteHostName
usdL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteHostName.description: The host name obtained during the tunnel establishment phase (via the Host Name AVP) of the L2TP peer. If the tunnel is idle, this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected, or a zero-length string if no name was previously known.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteVendorName.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteVendorName
usdL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteVendorName.description: Identifies the vendor name of the peer's L2TP implementation. If the tunnel is idle, this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected, of a zero-length string if no name was previously known.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteFirmwareRevisio.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteFirmwareRevision
usdL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteFirmwareRevisio.description: The tunnel peer's firmware revision number. If the tunnel is idle, this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected, or a zero value if no revision was previously known.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteProtocolVersion.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteProtocolVersion
usdL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteProtocolVersion.description: The protocol version and revision of the tunnel peer's implementation. The first octet contains the protocol version. The second octet contains the protocol revision.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteBearerCapabilit.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteBearerCapabilities
usdL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteBearerCapabilit.description: The Bearer Capabilities of the tunnel peer. If the tunnel is idle this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected, or 'none' if not previously known.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteFramingCapabili.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteFramingCapabilities
usdL2tpTunnelStatusRemoteFramingCapabili.description: The Framing Capabilities of the tunnel peer. If the tunnel is idle this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected, or 'none' if not previously known.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusSendWindowSize.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusSendWindowSize
usdL2tpTunnelStatusSendWindowSize.description: The tunnel peer's receive window size.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusSendQueueDepth.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusSendQueueDepth
usdL2tpTunnelStatusSendQueueDepth.description: Number of control packets on transmit queue.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusRecvSeq.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusRecvSeq
usdL2tpTunnelStatusRecvSeq.description: The next sequence number expected in a received control packet.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusRecvSeqAck.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusRecvSeqAck
usdL2tpTunnelStatusRecvSeqAck.description: The last received sequence number that was acknowledged back to the tunnel peer.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusSendSeq.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusSendSeq
usdL2tpTunnelStatusSendSeq.description: The next sequence number to be sent in a transmitted control packet.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusSendSeqAck.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusSendSeqAck
usdL2tpTunnelStatusSendSeqAck.description: The send sequence number that the tunnel peer has acknowledged. The flow control state can be determined by subtracting the usdL2tpTunnelStatusSendSeq from usdL2tpTunnelStatusSendSeqAck and comparing this value to usdL2tpTunnelStatusSendWindowSize.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusTotalSessions.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusTotalSessions
usdL2tpTunnelStatusTotalSessions.description: The total number of sessions that this tunnel has successfully connected through to its tunnel peer since this tunnel was created, including those that have since terminated.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusFailedSessions.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusFailedSessions
usdL2tpTunnelStatusFailedSessions.description: The number of sessions that were initiated but failed to reach the established phase.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusActiveSessions.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusActiveSessions
usdL2tpTunnelStatusActiveSessions.description: The current number of sessions in the established state.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusLastResultCode.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusLastResultCode
usdL2tpTunnelStatusLastResultCode.description: The last value of the result code as described in the Result Code AVP which caused the tunnel to disconnect.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusLastErrorCode.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusLastErrorCode
usdL2tpTunnelStatusLastErrorCode.description: The last value of the error code as described in the Result Code AVP which caused the tunnel to disconnect.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusLastErrorMessage.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusLastErrorMessage
usdL2tpTunnelStatusLastErrorMessage.description: The last value of the optional message as described in the Result Code AVP which caused the tunnel to disconnect.

usdL2tpTunnelStatusCumEstabTime.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatusCumEstabTime
usdL2tpTunnelStatusCumEstabTime.description: The cumulative time in seconds that this tunnel, since first being created, has spent in the established state (which may be punctuated by intervals outside the established state).

usdL2tpTunnelStatTable.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatTable
usdL2tpTunnelStatTable.description: The L2TP tunnel statistics table. Describes the control and payload statistics for each L2TP tunnel. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in usdL2tpTunnelConfigTable.

usdL2tpTunnelStatEntry.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatEntry
usdL2tpTunnelStatEntry.description: Describes the L2TP control and payload statistics for an L2TP tunnel.

usdL2tpTunnelStatIfIndex.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatIfIndex
usdL2tpTunnelStatIfIndex.description: Same value as ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvErrors.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvErrors
usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvErrors.description: Number of control packets incurring reception errors.

usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvDiscards.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvDiscards
usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvDiscards.description: Number of control packets discarded after reception.

usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendErrors.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendErrors
usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendErrors.description: Number of control packets incurring transmission errors.

usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendDiscards.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendDiscards
usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendDiscards.description: Number of control packets discarded before transmission.

usdL2tpTunnelStatPayRecvErrors.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatPayRecvErrors
usdL2tpTunnelStatPayRecvErrors.description: Number of payload packets incurring reception errors.

usdL2tpTunnelStatPayRecvDiscards.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatPayRecvDiscards
usdL2tpTunnelStatPayRecvDiscards.description: Number of payload packets discarded after reception.

usdL2tpTunnelStatPaySendErrors.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatPaySendErrors
usdL2tpTunnelStatPaySendErrors.description: Number of payload packets incurring transmission errors.

usdL2tpTunnelStatPaySendDiscards.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatPaySendDiscards
usdL2tpTunnelStatPaySendDiscards.description: Number of payload packets discarded before transmission.

usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvZLB.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvZLB
usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvZLB.description: Number of Zero Length Body control packet acknowledgement packets that were received.

usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvOutOfSequence.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvOutOfSequence
usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvOutOfSequence.description: Number of control packets not received in the correct sequence number order.

usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvOutOfWindow.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvOutOfWindow
usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlRecvOutOfWindow.description: Number of control packets received outside the offered receive window.

usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendZLB.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendZLB
usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendZLB.description: Number of Zero Length Body control packets sent.

usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendRetransmits.name: usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendRetransmits
usdL2tpTunnelStatCtlSendRetransmits.description: Number of control packet send retransmissions.

usdL2tpMapTifSidToSifEntry.name: usdL2tpMapTifSidToSifEntry
usdL2tpMapTifSidToSifEntry.description: A mapping of TunnelIf/SessionId to SessionIf.

usdL2tpMapTifSidToSifTunnelIfIndex.name: usdL2tpMapTifSidToSifTunnelIfIndex
usdL2tpMapTifSidToSifTunnelIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of a tunnel interface.

usdL2tpMapTifSidToSifLocalSessionId.name: usdL2tpMapTifSidToSifLocalSessionId
usdL2tpMapTifSidToSifLocalSessionId.description: A local session ID on the associated tunnel interface.

usdL2tpMapTifSidToSifSessionIfIndex.name: usdL2tpMapTifSidToSifSessionIfIndex
usdL2tpMapTifSidToSifSessionIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the session interface identified by this entry's Tunnel ifIndex and local Session Id pair.

usdL2tpMapTidToTifTable.name: usdL2tpMapTidToTifTable
usdL2tpMapTidToTifTable.description: Map L2TP tunnel IDs to tunnel interfaces.

usdL2tpMapTidToTifEntry.name: usdL2tpMapTidToTifEntry
usdL2tpMapTidToTifEntry.description: A mapping of L2TP tunnel ID to tunnel interface.

usdL2tpMapTidToTifIfIndex.name: usdL2tpMapTidToTifIfIndex
usdL2tpMapTidToTifIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the tunnel interface having the associated tunnel identifier.

usdL2tpSessionConfigTable.name: usdL2tpSessionConfigTable
usdL2tpSessionConfigTable.description: The L2TP session configuration table. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in usdL2tpSessionStatsTable.

usdL2tpSessionConfigEntry.name: usdL2tpSessionConfigEntry
usdL2tpSessionConfigEntry.description: Describes the configuration attributes of an L2TP session.

usdL2tpSessionConfigIfIndex.name: usdL2tpSessionConfigIfIndex
usdL2tpSessionConfigIfIndex.description: Same value as ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

usdL2tpSessionConfigRowStatus.name: usdL2tpSessionConfigRowStatus
usdL2tpSessionConfigRowStatus.description: An implementation may choose not to support administrative configuration of tunnels.

usdL2tpSessionStatusTable.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusTable
usdL2tpSessionStatusTable.description: The L2TP session status and statistics table.

usdL2tpSessionStatusEntry.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusEntry
usdL2tpSessionStatusEntry.description: An L2TP session interface status and statistics entry.

usdL2tpSessionStatusIfIndex.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusIfIndex
usdL2tpSessionStatusIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an L2TP session interface.

usdL2tpSessionStatusLacPppIfIndex.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusLacPppIfIndex
usdL2tpSessionStatusLacPppIfIndex.description: For pass-through PPP sessions (conventional LAC), the ifIndex of an associated local PPP interface through which the remote LAC client was connected. If unknown, this object contains a value of zero. For locally originated PPP sessions (LNS-like), this object has a value of zero. This object is deprecated in favor of usdL2tpSessionStatusLacTunneledIfIndex.

usdL2tpSessionStatusLocalSessionId.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusLocalSessionId
usdL2tpSessionStatusLocalSessionId.description: The local session ID for the session.

usdL2tpSessionStatusRemoteSessionId.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusRemoteSessionId
usdL2tpSessionStatusRemoteSessionId.description: The remote session ID for the session.

usdL2tpSessionStatusUserName.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusUserName
usdL2tpSessionStatusUserName.description: The peer session name on this interface, typically the login name of the remote user. If the user name is unknown this object will contain a zero-length string.

usdL2tpSessionStatusEffectiveAdminState.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusEffectiveAdminState
usdL2tpSessionStatusEffectiveAdminState.description: The administrative state currently in effect. This could be the configured admin state for this session, or an overriding admin state exerted from a higher hierarchical level (system, destination, tunnel).

usdL2tpSessionStatusState.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusState
usdL2tpSessionStatusState.description: The current state of the session.

usdL2tpSessionStatusCallType.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusCallType
usdL2tpSessionStatusCallType.description: The type of call and role this tunnel peer is providing for this session. For example, lacIncoming(1) indicates this tunnel peer is acting as a LAC and generated a Incoming-Call-Request to the tunnel peer (the LNS). Note that tunnel peers can be both LAC and LNS simultaneously.

usdL2tpSessionStatusCallSerialNumber.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusCallSerialNumber
usdL2tpSessionStatusCallSerialNumber.description: The serial number assigned to this session.

usdL2tpSessionStatusTxConnectSpeed.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusTxConnectSpeed
usdL2tpSessionStatusTxConnectSpeed.description: The last known transmit baud rate for this session.

usdL2tpSessionStatusRxConnectSpeed.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusRxConnectSpeed
usdL2tpSessionStatusRxConnectSpeed.description: The last known receive baud rate for this session.

usdL2tpSessionStatusCallBearerType.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusCallBearerType
usdL2tpSessionStatusCallBearerType.description: The bearer type of this session.

usdL2tpSessionStatusFramingType.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusFramingType
usdL2tpSessionStatusFramingType.description: The framing type of this session.

usdL2tpSessionStatusPhysChanId.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusPhysChanId
usdL2tpSessionStatusPhysChanId.description: The physical channel identifier for the session. For pass-through PPP sessions, typically the ifIndex of the access interface lying below the PPP interface identified by usdL2tpSessionStatusLacTunneledIfIndex.

usdL2tpSessionStatusDnis.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusDnis
usdL2tpSessionStatusDnis.description: The Dialed Number Information String that the LAC obtained from the network for the session. If no DNIS was provided, a zero-length string will be returned.

usdL2tpSessionStatusClid.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusClid
usdL2tpSessionStatusClid.description: The Calling Line ID that the LAC obtained from the network for the session. If no CLID was provided, a zero-length string will be returned.

usdL2tpSessionStatusSubAddress.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusSubAddress
usdL2tpSessionStatusSubAddress.description: The SubAddress that the LAC obtained from the network for the session. If no SubAddress was provided, a zero-length string will be returned.

usdL2tpSessionStatusPrivateGroupId.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusPrivateGroupId
usdL2tpSessionStatusPrivateGroupId.description: The Private Group Identifier used for this tunneled session. If no Private Group Identifier was provided, a zero-length string will be returned.

usdL2tpSessionStatusProxyLcp.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusProxyLcp
usdL2tpSessionStatusProxyLcp.description: Indicates whether the LAC performed proxy LCP for this session.

usdL2tpSessionStatusAuthMethod.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusAuthMethod
usdL2tpSessionStatusAuthMethod.description: The proxy authentication method employed by the LAC for the session. If usdL2tpSessionProxyLcp is false(2) this object reports a value of 'none' and should be ignored.

usdL2tpSessionStatusSequencingState.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusSequencingState
usdL2tpSessionStatusSequencingState.description: Indicates which tunnel peers have requested payload sequencing.

usdL2tpSessionStatusRecvSeq.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusRecvSeq
usdL2tpSessionStatusRecvSeq.description: The next receive sequence number expected.

usdL2tpSessionStatusLacTunneledIfIndex.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusLacTunneledIfIndex
usdL2tpSessionStatusLacTunneledIfIndex.description: For pass-through remote client sessions (conventional LAC), the ifIndex of an associated local interface through which the remote LAC client was connected. If unknown, this object contains a value of zero. For locally originated sessions (LNS-like), this object has a value of zero.

usdL2tpSessionStatusCumEstabTime.name: usdL2tpSessionStatusCumEstabTime
usdL2tpSessionStatusCumEstabTime.description: The cumulative time in seconds that this session, since first being created, has spent in the established state (which may be punctuated by intervals outside the established state).

usdL2tpSessionStatEntry.name: usdL2tpSessionStatEntry
usdL2tpSessionStatEntry.description: An L2TP session interface statistics entry.

usdL2tpSessionStatIfIndex.name: usdL2tpSessionStatIfIndex
usdL2tpSessionStatIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an L2TP session interface.

usdL2tpSessionStatPayRecvErrors.name: usdL2tpSessionStatPayRecvErrors
usdL2tpSessionStatPayRecvErrors.description: Number of payload packets incurring reception errors.

usdL2tpSessionStatPayRecvDiscards.name: usdL2tpSessionStatPayRecvDiscards
usdL2tpSessionStatPayRecvDiscards.description: Number of payload packets discarded after reception.

usdL2tpSessionStatPaySendErrors.name: usdL2tpSessionStatPaySendErrors
usdL2tpSessionStatPaySendErrors.description: Number of payload packets incurring transmission errors.

usdL2tpSessionStatPaySendDiscards.name: usdL2tpSessionStatPaySendDiscards
usdL2tpSessionStatPaySendDiscards.description: Number of payload packets discarded before transmission.

usdL2tpSessionStatRecvOutOfSequence.name: usdL2tpSessionStatRecvOutOfSequence
usdL2tpSessionStatRecvOutOfSequence.description: The number of packets received out of sequence.

usdL2tpSessionStatResequencingTimeouts.name: usdL2tpSessionStatResequencingTimeouts
usdL2tpSessionStatResequencingTimeouts.description: The number of reassembly timeouts that have occurred.

usdL2tpSessionStatPayLostPackets.name: usdL2tpSessionStatPayLostPackets
usdL2tpSessionStatPayLostPackets.description: When sequence numbers are enabled, this value represents the estimated number of payload packets lost, based on observed gaps in sequence numbers. This estimate is subject to correction (decrement) upon receipt of out-of-sequence packets that fill previously observed gaps.

usdL2tpUdpIpDestTable.name: usdL2tpUdpIpDestTable
usdL2tpUdpIpDestTable.description: The L2TP UDP/IP destination table. Reports the UDP/IP characteristics of a L2TP UDP/IP destination. More specific UDP/IP detail per tunnel is reported in the usdL2tpUdpIpTunnelTable.
